cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a probabilistic autoregressive model for graph generation, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves modeling complex distributions, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
